%N A395834 Digits of the 10-adic integer x satisfying x = 1 + 10*x^2.
%H A395834 Paul D. Hanna, <a href="/A395834/b395834.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..1000</a>
%e A395834 x = ...5536362092014529544671708888060625632063569426345211
%e A395834 where x = 1 + 10*x^2.
%e A395834 This constant equals the 10-adic sum involving the Catalan numbers:
%e A395834 x = 1 + 1*10 + 2*10^2 + 5*10^3 + 14*10^4 + 42*10^5 + 132*10^6 + 429*10^7 + ... + A000108(n)*10^n + ...
%e A395834 Also, x = (1 - y)/20 where a 10-adic integer value of y = sqrt(-39) (y^2 = ...999999961) is y = -...727241840290590893434177761212512641271388526904219.
%o A395834 (PARI) \\ Displays N digits
%o A395834 upto(N) = {CAT = (1 - sqrt(1-4*x +x^2*O(x^(2*N))))/(2*x);
%o A395834 CAT10 = subst(truncate(CAT),x,10);
%o A395834 DIGITS = Vecrev(digits(CAT10%(10^N)))}
%o A395834 upto(100)
%Y A395834 Cf. A000108, A018247, A120817.
%K A395834 nonn,base,new
%O A395834 0,3
